---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ToolPageCta from '../../components/ToolPageCta.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';

const faq = [
  {
    question: "What is the difference between SOC2 Type I and Type II?",
    answer: "SOC2 Type I is a point-in-time assessment — an auditor evaluates whether your controls are suitably designed as of a specific date. It's faster to obtain (2-4 months) and less expensive, but provides less assurance to customers. SOC2 Type II covers a period of time (typically 6-12 months) and assesses whether controls were operating effectively throughout that period. Type II is what enterprise customers require because it proves sustained, not just designed, security practices. Most SaaS companies start with Type I as a stepping stone while building toward Type II."
  },
  {
    question: "How long does SOC2 Type II take?",
    answer: "A full SOC2 Type II audit typically takes 9-18 months from decision to report. The timeline includes: 1-2 months for readiness assessment, 3-6 months of control implementation and evidence collection, 6-12 months of observation period (the actual audit window auditors examine), and 1-2 months for auditor fieldwork and report writing. With automated compliance tools like Vanta or Drata, the evidence collection phase can be reduced significantly. Rushing the observation period is not possible — auditors need a minimum window (usually 6 months) to verify sustained control operation."
  },
  {
    question: "What are the Common Criteria controls (CC6.1, CC7.1, etc.)?",
    answer: "The Common Criteria (CC) are the Security Trust Service Criterion controls — the most critical category, required for all SOC2 reports. CC6.x covers logical and physical access controls: CC6.1 is about restricting access to authorized users, CC6.2 covers authentication, CC6.3 is role-based access, CC6.6 covers network security, and CC6.7 is about data transmission security. CC7.x covers system operations and anomaly detection. CC8.x covers change management. Each control requires both a policy document and evidence of implementation (access review records, MFA enrollment screenshots, firewall rules, etc.)."
  },
  {
    question: "Which automated tools help with SOC2 compliance?",
    answer: "The three main automated compliance platforms are: Vanta (best for startups, integrates with 100+ tools, ~$20k-$40k/year), Drata (strong automation and Slack integration, similar pricing), and Secureframe (slightly more affordable, good for smaller teams). All three connect to AWS/GCP/Azure, GitHub, Okta, and other tools to automatically collect evidence and flag non-compliant controls. They also provide auditor portals that make the fieldwork phase significantly faster. Tugboat Logic (acquired by OneTrust) is another option for larger enterprises. The ROI is clear: manual SOC2 evidence collection takes hundreds of hours vs. automated platforms."
  },
  {
    question: "Does SOC2 require annual penetration testing?",
    answer: "SOC2 does not technically mandate penetration testing, but it is expected by most auditors under the Availability and Security criteria (particularly CC7.1 and CC7.2 around anomaly detection and risk assessment). In practice, nearly every SOC2 Type II audit expects evidence of at least one external penetration test per audit period, and enterprise customers reading your report will look for it. The penetration test scope should cover your production environment, APIs, and web application. A report from a reputable firm (not an automated scanner) is required. Budget $10k-$30k for a professional pentest depending on scope."
  },
  {
    question: "How much does a SOC2 Type II audit cost?",
    answer: "SOC2 Type II audit costs vary significantly by auditor and company size. A typical range is: $15k-$30k for small startups (< 50 employees, simple infrastructure) with a boutique CPA firm; $30k-$60k for mid-size companies; $60k-$150k+ for large enterprises with complex environments and Big 4 or major audit firms. These costs exclude the compliance platform ($20k-$40k/year), penetration testing ($10k-$30k), and internal engineering time (often 200-500 hours). Total first-year cost for a startup is commonly $80k-$150k when factoring all-in costs."
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="SOC2 Compliance Checklist for Developers: Type I vs Type II Guide"
  description="SOC2 Type II compliance checklist for dev teams: Trust Service Criteria, access controls, encryption, logging, incident response, vendor management, and audit preparation."
  tool="SOC2, compliance, Type I Type II, Trust Service Criteria, audit, access control, security compliance"
  faq={faq}
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "WebPage",
    "name": "SOC2 Compliance Checklist for Developers: Type I vs Type II Guide",
    "url": "https://devplaybook.cc/tools/soc2-compliance-checklist",
    "description": "SOC2 Type II compliance checklist for dev teams: Trust Service Criteria, access controls, encryption, logging, incident response, vendor management, and audit preparation.",
  })} />

  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">SOC2 Compliance Checklist for Developers: Type I vs Type II Guide</h1>
  <p class="text-text-muted mb-6">SOC2 (System and Organization Controls 2) is the security audit standard that enterprise customers require before trusting your SaaS product with their data. This checklist covers the Trust Service Criteria, what your engineering team needs to implement, automated tooling to reduce the manual burden, and what to expect from the audit process.</p>

  <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6 text-sm text-text-muted flex-wrap">
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> 5 Trust Service Criteria</span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Type I and Type II explained</span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Developer implementation checklist</span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Automated tools (Vanta / Drata)</span>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">SOC2 Type I vs Type II</h2>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
    <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
      <thead>
        <tr class="border-b border-border">
          <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">Dimension</th>
          <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">Type I</th>
          <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">Type II</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="text-text-muted">
        <tr class="border-b border-border/50"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Assessment window</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Point in time</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">6-12 month period</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-border/50"><td class="py-2 pr-4">What is assessed</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Control design</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Control effectiveness over time</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-border/50"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Time to achieve</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">3-6 months</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">9-18 months</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-border/50"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Cost (audit fees only)</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">$10k-$20k</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">$15k-$60k</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4">Enterprise acceptance</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Limited</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Required</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">The 5 Trust Service Criteria</h2>
  <p class="text-text-muted mb-4">SOC2 reports are built around Trust Service Criteria (TSC). <strong>Security</strong> is mandatory for all SOC2 reports. The other four are optional but commonly included:</p>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
    <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
      <thead>
        <tr class="border-b border-border">
          <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">Criterion</th>
          <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">What It Covers</th>
          <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">Required?</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="text-text-muted">
        <tr class="border-b border-border/50"><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium text-text">Security (CC)</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Access controls, encryption, logging, incident response</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Always</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-border/50"><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium text-text">Availability (A)</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Uptime SLAs, DR, capacity planning</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Common</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-border/50"><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium text-text">Confidentiality (C)</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Data classification, encryption, NDA enforcement</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Common</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-border/50"><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium text-text">Processing Integrity (PI)</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Accurate, timely, complete data processing</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">If processing financial/critical data</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium text-text">Privacy (P)</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">PII collection, use, retention, disposal</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">If handling PII</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">Developer Implementation Checklist</h2>
  <p class="text-text-muted mb-3"><strong>Access Control</strong></p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-muted mb-4 space-y-1">
    <li>MFA enforced for all production system access (AWS, GitHub, Okta)</li>
    <li>Least-privilege IAM roles — no standing admin access</li>
    <li>Quarterly access reviews with documented approvals</li>
    <li>Offboarding checklist with access revocation within 24 hours</li>
    <li>SSH keys rotated; no shared credentials</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="text-text-muted mb-3"><strong>Encryption</strong></p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-muted mb-4 space-y-1">
    <li>Encryption at rest: database volumes, S3 buckets, backups (AES-256)</li>
    <li>Encryption in transit: TLS 1.2+ enforced, HSTS headers set</li>
    <li>Secrets management: no secrets in git, use Vault/AWS Secrets Manager</li>
    <li>Key rotation policy documented and enforced</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="text-text-muted mb-3"><strong>Logging and Monitoring</strong></p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-muted mb-4 space-y-1">
    <li>Centralized logging (CloudWatch, Datadog, Splunk) with 1-year retention</li>
    <li>Audit logs for all authentication events and privilege changes</li>
    <li>Alerting on failed login attempts, anomalous API usage</li>
    <li>Log integrity protection — immutable log storage</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="text-text-muted mb-3"><strong>Vulnerability Management</strong></p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-muted mb-4 space-y-1">
    <li>Dependency scanning in CI (Dependabot, Snyk)</li>
    <li>Container image scanning (Trivy, ECR scanning)</li>
    <li>Annual external penetration test from a reputable firm</li>
    <li>CVE remediation SLAs: Critical ≤ 7 days, High ≤ 30 days</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="text-text-muted mb-3"><strong>Change Management</strong></p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-muted mb-4 space-y-1">
    <li>All production changes via PR with peer review</li>
    <li>Separate development, staging, and production environments</li>
    <li>Change approval policy documented</li>
    <li>Rollback procedures tested and documented</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">Automated Compliance Platforms</h2>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
    <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
      <thead>
        <tr class="border-b border-border">
          <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">Platform</th>
          <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">Strengths</th>
          <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">Price (est.)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="text-text-muted">
        <tr class="border-b border-border/50"><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium text-text">Vanta</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">100+ integrations, strong startup focus</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">$20k-$40k/yr</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-border/50"><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium text-text">Drata</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">High automation, Slack-native</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">$20k-$40k/yr</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-border/50"><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium text-text">Secureframe</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">More affordable, good UI</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">$10k-$25k/yr</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium text-text">Tugboat Logic</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Enterprise, acquired by OneTrust</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Custom</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">Common Audit Failures</h2>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-muted mb-6 space-y-1">
    <li><strong>Missing access reviews</strong>: Quarterly reviews must be documented with approver sign-off, not just assumed</li>
    <li><strong>Incomplete offboarding evidence</strong>: Need ticketing records showing access was revoked</li>
    <li><strong>Security training gaps</strong>: All employees must complete annual security awareness training with completion records</li>
    <li><strong>Unscoped vendor management</strong>: Sub-processors handling customer data need documented risk assessments</li>
    <li><strong>No incident response test</strong>: IR plan must be tested (tabletop exercise) at least annually</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">SOC2 vs ISO 27001</h2>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
    <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
      <thead>
        <tr class="border-b border-border">
          <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">Feature</th>
          <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">SOC2</th>
          <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 font-semibold">ISO 27001</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="text-text-muted">
        <tr class="border-b border-border/50"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Standard body</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">AICPA (US)</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">ISO/IEC (International)</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-border/50"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Market</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">US enterprise buyers</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">EU, APAC enterprise</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-border/50"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Output</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Attestation report (shared)</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Certification (public)</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4">Renewal</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Annual audit</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">3-year cert + annual surveillance</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <ToolPageCta />
  <FaqSection faqs={faq} />
</BaseLayout>
